  "title": "Senior/Specialist, Procurement",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Be familiar with fresh produce (especially vegetables) and select suitable product assortments based on different business scenarios.</li><li>Possess strong knowledge of wholesale markets and supplier resources; independently source and develop new products to meet procurement targets.</li><li>Build and manage supplier portfolios, control procurement costs, and maintain competitive retail pricing.</li><li>Develop appropriate warehousing and distribution solutions based on product characteristics to minimize loss and wastage.</li><li>Monitor market trends, manage purchase and selling prices, and formulate promotional plans as well as sales and profit targets for assigned categories.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>At least <strong>3-4 years of procurement experience</strong>, with strong local supplier networks preferred.</li><li>Familiar with procurement processes, including <strong>price negotiation, order management, accounts handling, and supplier development</strong>.</li><li>Strong data analysis skills with good computer proficiency.</li><li>Excellent communication and coordination skills, able to work cross-functionally and drive execution.</li><li>Positive work attitude, hardworking, and able to adapt to overtime when required.</li></ul>",
